'''Ras Boutria''' or '''Ras Bou Tria''' is a [[cape|head land]] of the [[east]]ern coast of [[Tunisia]] that marks the northern tip of the [[governorate of Sfax]].<ref>Barrington Atlas, 2000, pl. 33 H2.</ref>  On the shore there is the archaeological site of ancient [[Acholla]], a [[Roman Empire|Roman]] city of [[Roman North Africa|Africa Proconsularis]] with [[ruins]] of [[Roman Villa|houses]] Roman [[amphitheater]] and [[bath house|bath]]s, and the cities of Louâtre Louzes nearby.<ref>http://mapcarta.com/17289518</ref><ref>[http://www.getamap.net/maps/tunisia/safaqis/_boutria_ras/ Ras Bou tria]</ref> it is located at 35°4'33" N and 11°1'40" E.

