'''Sverre Arnljot Breste Kjeldstadli''' (14 February 1916 – 28 March 1961) was a Norwegian historian.
During [[World War II]] he was a courier for [[Milorg]]. His [[dr.philos.]] thesis from 1959, ''Hjemmestyrkene. Hovedtrekk av den militære motstanden under okkupasjonen'', has been an inspiration for later works by other historians.<ref name=kl>{{cite encyclopedia |first=Øystein |last=Sørensen |encyclopedia=[[Norsk krigsleksikon 1940-45]] |title=Kjeldstadli, Sverre |language=Norwegian |editor=[[Hans Fredrik Dahl|Dahl]] |editor2=[[Guri Hjeltnes|Hjeltnes]] |editor3=[[Berit Nøkleby|Nøkleby]] |editor4=[[Nils Johan Ringdal|Ringdal]] |editor5=[[Øystein Sørensen|Sørensen]] |url=http://mediabase1.uib.no/krigslex/k/k2.html#kjeldstadli-sverre |accessdate=26 January 2010 |year=1995 |publisher=Cappelen |location=Oslo |isbn=82-02-14138-9 |page=214 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120315115059/http://mediabase1.uib.no/krigslex/k/k2.html#kjeldstadli-sverre |archivedate=15 March 2012 |df= }}</ref>
He was a son of trade unionist [[Lars Kjeldstadli]] (1870–1934) and his wife Beate, (born Lotsberg, (1880–1965). He was a son-in-law of [[Daniel Grini]],<ref>{{cite book|last=Kjeldstadli|first=Knut|authorlink=Knut Kjeldstadli|title=Mine fire besteforeldre|publisher=Pax|location=Oslo|date=2010|page=|isbn=978-82-530-3342-6|language=Norwegian}}</ref> and together with Ellen Helvig Grini (1918–2001) he had the son, historian [[Knut Kjeldstadli]].<ref name=nbl-knut>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Knut Kjeldstadli |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Jan Eivind |last=Myhre |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Knut_Kjeldstadli/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=26 January 2010}}</ref> He died in March 1961 and was buried in [[Ullern]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disnorge.no/gravminner/index.php?language=engelsk|title=Cemeteries in Norway|publisher=DIS-Norge|accessdate=5 July 2011|postscript=([http://www.disnorge.no/gravminner/bilde.php?id=3282268 image of tombstone])}}</ref>
